le activates the PP2A<sup>Cdc55</sup> inhibitors <sd-pretag id="sdPretag812795467sd" parent-tag-id="45">Igo1</sd-pretag> and <sd-pretag id="sdPretag223912963sd" parent-tag-id="46">Igo2</sd-pretag> via phosphorylation at key regulatory sites (right). The resulting inhibition of the phosphatase is essential to tip the balance towards increased net phosphorylation. <graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?panel_id=118094"/></sd-panel></fig></article>